benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/admin/invoices - Trigger an invoice generation for all parked accounts

covered: POST - Valid Request scenarios covered with 200 OK responses for default, offset/limit, and headers.
POST - Empty data scenario covered (no parked accounts) with 200 and indication of no invoices generated.
POST - Pagination and query parameters coverage (offset, limit, default limit, max limit, extra params).
POST - Authorization and authentication errors covered (missing/invalid header; unauthorized token leading to 401/403).
POST - Validation coverage for invalid parameter values (negative, zero or non-integer offset/limit).
POST - Large payload/volume handling (large numbers of parked accounts, limit up to 1000, and huge datasets).
POST - Server error handling covered (503 when backend/service unavailable).
POST - Edge-case handling for extra unexpected query parameters (ignored or error).
POST - Security testing against header injection attempts (no sensitive information leaked).
POST - Recovery from transient network failures (retry semantics).
Post - Regression tests for header parsing and backward compatibility covered (TC16/TC17).
Post - Performance under concurrency and accessibility tests (TC18/TC19).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling scenarios not covered.
Payload body validation not applicable if body is not used; consider adding explicit payload tests if payloads are introduced.
recommendations: Add tests for duplicate submissions to ensure idempotency.
Add rate limiting tests to verify throttling behavior.
Add caching behavior tests including ETag and Cache-Control headers.
If any payload is introduced in future, add tests for valid/invalid payload structures and data types.
